WEBVTT

00:03.588 --> 00:07.706
We're in the car, honey.
We're going to
the hospital for tests.

00:15.433 --> 00:19.267
We're in the hospital.
We're going to
the doctor's office.

00:25.985 --> 00:27.441
Can you tell me
what this is called?

00:30.156 --> 00:32.442
You use it
to get food
from inside.

00:32.575 --> 00:34.281
Yes, but
what's it called?

00:35.953 --> 00:37.454
Is it a spatula?

00:37.538 --> 00:38.948
No.

00:39.081 --> 00:40.821
Good.
Is it a can opener?

00:40.958 --> 00:45.247
No. It's... lt's...

00:47.798 --> 00:49.663
You're trying to
make me look stupid.

00:50.801 --> 00:54.089
You can go to hell!
Why don't you
kill yourself?

00:54.180 --> 00:55.636
Andres.

00:57.350 --> 00:58.931
It's okay.

01:01.479 --> 01:02.810
(CHUCKLES)

01:03.356 --> 01:04.937
There she is.

01:05.441 --> 01:07.056
Here I am.

01:07.151 --> 01:08.266
Here. Come on.

01:13.324 --> 01:15.485
You just need to answer
a few more questions,

01:15.618 --> 01:17.483
then we're going home.
We'll have lunch, okay?

01:18.204 --> 01:19.364
Okay.

01:22.667 --> 01:23.827
I'm sorry.

01:25.962 --> 01:27.827
l have Alzheimer's.

01:28.339 --> 01:30.000
I know.

01:30.383 --> 01:35.127
The mood swings
come on quickly,
but it's under control.

01:35.221 --> 01:38.509
Don't worry.
He's actually perfect
for the drug trial.

01:39.517 --> 01:41.053
Oh. (SIGHS)
(CHUCKLES)

01:42.353 --> 01:43.388
Thank God.

01:43.521 --> 01:45.352
We can start as
soon as next week.

01:45.690 --> 01:47.021
(COUGHING)

01:49.318 --> 01:51.855
Andres! Oh, my God!

01:53.823 --> 01:55.233
Andres?

02:30.234 --> 02:30.268
FOREMAN: Early onset
familial Alzheimer's.
Brazilian descent.

02:30.276 --> 02:33.313
FOREMAN: Early onset
familial Alzheimer's.
Brazilian descent.

02:33.404 --> 02:34.894
Blood chemistries
showed high ammonia.

02:35.406 --> 02:38.398
Vomiting stopped
after the ER put him
on antiemetics.

02:38.492 --> 02:40.232
Any recent
heaHhissues?

02:40.369 --> 02:43.076
Just a sore throat
a few weeks ago.

02:43.205 --> 02:45.662
How advanced is he?
Could be hyperalimentation.

02:45.750 --> 02:47.741
Advanced enough,
but no N feedings.

02:47.877 --> 02:50.084
The wife shut down
her floral company
to stay home

02:50.171 --> 02:52.412
and feed him
every meal he's had
in the last four years.

02:52.506 --> 02:54.337
Do we owe this case
to your guilt

02:54.425 --> 02:56.507
at having ignored
your own forgetful mommy?

02:56.594 --> 02:58.676
My guilt over my mom
is why I put up
with my dad.

02:58.763 --> 02:59.843
You're taking this case

02:59.930 --> 03:02.182
because we're running
a Phase Two trial on
an Alzheimer's drug.

03:02.266 --> 03:04.928
You couldn't round up enough
doddering, old guinea pigs,

03:05.061 --> 03:06.847
so you need us to
fix this little piggy?

03:06.937 --> 03:10.179
I'd like to sit in.
Especially since you're
short a team member.

03:10.274 --> 03:11.855
You mean Taub?
Got him in here.

03:11.942 --> 03:14.103
He asked for personal days.
His daughter's sick.

03:14.236 --> 03:16.613
Isn't that the point
of having a spare?

03:16.697 --> 03:18.107
l denied his request.

03:18.199 --> 03:19.780
After I'd already
approved it,

03:19.867 --> 03:21.368
which you knew because
I sent you a memo.

03:23.287 --> 03:27.872
Dr. Adams,
taped under your chair
is an index card.

03:27.958 --> 03:29.289
Would you read it,
please?

03:38.219 --> 03:40.460
"Wednesday, 2:43 pm.

03:40.554 --> 03:44.547
"A black pawn will believe
he's the black king

03:44.642 --> 03:48.635
"and attempt to capture
the white head
of diagnostics."

03:50.481 --> 03:52.437
lt's 10:15 on Friday.

03:52.525 --> 03:55.892
Damn it. (SIGHS)
Look, the point is,
I saw this coming.

03:56.570 --> 03:58.947
Dr. Foreman and I
did not always
see eye to eye,

03:59.031 --> 04:00.942
but he never had
the power to overrule me.

04:01.033 --> 04:02.273
Now that
he has the power,

04:02.368 --> 04:04.609
he won't be able to resist
the temptation to use it.

04:04.703 --> 04:07.615
With great power
comes great micromanaging.

04:07.706 --> 04:08.991
And great vests.

04:09.083 --> 04:11.665
I know you're
the better diagnostician.

04:11.752 --> 04:13.743
I'm not gonna interfere.
I'm only here to help.

04:13.838 --> 04:16.545
Could be
transient nitrogen load
from a GI bleed.

04:16.632 --> 04:18.042
Not if the vomiting's
persistent.

04:18.134 --> 04:21.547
Which we won't know,
because the ER put him
on antiemetics.

04:21.637 --> 04:22.592
Take him off.

04:22.680 --> 04:24.045
Wait. He was
puking his guts out.

04:24.140 --> 04:26.005
We'd risk aspiration.

04:28.269 --> 04:30.100
I'm just disagreeing,
not overruling.

04:30.771 --> 04:34.355
So glad you're on board.
Take him off antiemetics.

04:34.442 --> 04:36.353
Do an upper endoscopy
to check for bleeds.

04:42.658 --> 04:44.523
It could be
a bladder infection.

04:44.618 --> 04:45.824
We'll run
a pregnancy test.

04:45.911 --> 04:47.162
I'm not pregnant.

04:47.246 --> 04:49.578
Any type of birth control
can fail.

04:49.665 --> 04:50.950
Not mine.

04:53.586 --> 04:56.248
Oh, I'm sorry. You said
you were married?

04:56.338 --> 04:57.464
Yeah. Happily.

04:58.340 --> 05:03.255
It's okay. Sex can wane
in any marriage over time.

05:03.345 --> 05:05.381
No, no.
We've never had sex.

05:06.765 --> 05:10.804
We kiss and cuddle,
but neither one of us
is interested in sex.

05:12.813 --> 05:15.225
You're both celibate?

05:15.316 --> 05:17.307
No, neither of us.

05:17.401 --> 05:20.564
Celibacy is a choice.
This is our orientation.

05:21.989 --> 05:23.069
We're asexual.

05:26.368 --> 05:29.826
Not quite sure what box
to check here.

05:29.914 --> 05:31.120
CHASE:
You’re making a mistake.

05:31.207 --> 05:32.868
If I had the power
to veto him,

05:32.958 --> 05:35.210
given all the crap
I've put up with
over the years,

05:35.294 --> 05:36.659
I don't know if
I could use it
objectively.

05:36.754 --> 05:37.789
I do.

05:37.880 --> 05:39.336
lcan.lhave.

05:39.798 --> 05:43.006
It might be easier
if you'd stay out
of the room.

05:43.093 --> 05:46.381
I thought
it'd be different.
This week.

05:46.472 --> 05:50.181
I'm supposed to talk
to his PO about getting
his ankle monitor off early.

05:50.267 --> 05:51.677
You're saying
he should defer
to you?

05:51.769 --> 05:54.761
No. I'm just saying
what he's doing
doesn't seem rational,

05:54.855 --> 05:58.313
which makes me think
it's rational in a way
I'm not privy to.

05:58.400 --> 06:00.140
He always has a plan.

06:00.236 --> 06:02.147
And he's always
self-destructive.

06:02.238 --> 06:05.401
He may just be
shooting himself
in the ankle.

06:12.331 --> 06:16.244
I know it feels strange.
Dr. Chase is just looking
in your throat.

06:16.335 --> 06:18.667
We're in the hospital.
You're fine.

06:20.047 --> 06:21.912
That's a pretty nice
trophy there, Andres.

06:22.007 --> 06:23.508
NATALIE:
He coached youth soccer.

06:23.592 --> 06:25.173
Took a team that
was zero-and-six

06:25.261 --> 06:27.547
all the way
to the state finals
at Long Branch.

06:33.811 --> 06:35.142
Hey, thanks for
doing this in here.

06:35.229 --> 06:37.561
Switching rooms can
be very disorienting.

06:37.648 --> 06:38.979
You take very
good care of him.

06:39.608 --> 06:42.315
I love him.
Sickness and health, right?

06:42.403 --> 06:45.736
Upper esophagus is clear,
moving on to the GE junction.

06:45.823 --> 06:46.812
